          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DefineEnergySourceUnit",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to determine and return the unit of measurement for a given energy source based on specific input parameters."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is low. Scalar functions typically involve straightforward logic, such as conditional statements or simple calculations, and operate on a single set of input values to produce a single output."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function takes one or more input parameters that are used to identify the energy source and determine the appropriate unit of measurement. Each parameter serves a specific purpose, such as:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@EnergySourceID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": An identifier for the energy source, which is used to look up or determine the corresponding unit of measurement."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
