                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "IF",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ") to map specific energy source identifiers to their respective units."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Returning a default unit if the input does not match any predefined conditions."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The workflow is linear and involves checking the input against known conditions to produce the output."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can introduce performance overhead when used in large queries, especially if they are called repeatedly for each row in a result set. This is because scalar functions are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower query performance compared to set-based operations. To mitigate this, consider:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
